# BiteSites environment variables
#
# Copy to .env.local and fill in as needed:  cp .env.example .env.local
#
# The VITE_FIREBASE_* values are OPTIONAL. src/lib/firebase.js already ships the
# bitesites-org project's public web config as a default, so a fresh clone builds
# and runs with no setup. Set these only to point a build at a different project
# (a staging environment, for example).
#
# A Firebase web config is public by design — it identifies the project, it does
# not authorise anything. Access control is enforced by firestore.rules. Do not
# put a service-account key or any Admin SDK credential in this file or any other
# VITE_-prefixed variable: everything prefixed with VITE_ is inlined into the
# browser bundle and is readable by anyone.

# VITE_FIREBASE_API_KEY=
# VITE_FIREBASE_AUTH_DOMAIN=
# VITE_FIREBASE_PROJECT_ID=
# VITE_FIREBASE_STORAGE_BUCKET=
# VITE_FIREBASE_MESSAGING_SENDER_ID=
# VITE_FIREBASE_APP_ID=

# --- App Check (spam protection for the public lead form) --------------------
# Already configured and enforced. The live reCAPTCHA Enterprise site key ships
# as the default in src/lib/firebase.js — like the Firebase config, a reCAPTCHA
# site key is public by design. Override only for a separate environment.
# VITE_RECAPTCHA_SITE_KEY=

# Local development only. `localhost` is a registered reCAPTCHA domain, so the
# normal flow works in dev — you need this ONLY if attestation starts failing
# locally (e.g. on a LAN IP or a tunnel URL).
#
# Set to `true`, run `npm run dev`, and the SDK prints a debug token to the
# browser console. Register that token under App Check > Apps > Manage debug
# tokens, then paste it back here in place of `true`.
# VITE_APPCHECK_DEBUG_TOKEN=true

# Postmark settings are server-only and belong in the Functions environment, not
# this Vite file. See FIREBASE_SETUP.md. In particular, never add the Postmark
# server token here or to any variable beginning with VITE_.
